HEADWORD: Hexabasic
<hw>Hex`a*ba"sic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Hexa-</ets>
+ <ets>basic</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Having six hydrogen
atoms or six radicals capable of being replaced or saturated by bases;
-- said of acids; <as>as, mellitic acid is
<ex>hexabasic</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
